I find that people are more likely to find happiness if they focus on others is that personally seeking out happiness can be detrimental to those seeking out happiness for themselves. My grandfather said that finding happiness is like finding a treasure. Most seek out the treasure by trying to obtain a map of knowledge or by following a prescription given by others. For those who find this map, they must also seek out the treasure. Oftentimes, when seeking out this treasure, they throw out portions of their lives. They disregard their health, sacrifice their families, and are not attentive for their children. When they finally find the treasure, they cannot enjoy it because they have thrown out so many portions of their lives. They are unhappy because they can share their happiness with no one.
